"n.枴杖；v.支撑 【考】 crutch : walk / glasses : see(枴杖协助走路/眼镜 协助观看) n. 枴杖(长度达腋窝, 成对使用的那种); 支撑物 【记】cr哭, u一个大坑, tch = teach教: 掉进一个大坑里, 瘸了, 然后我就得教你使用－枴杖 【类】crutch: walk = glasses: see 枴杖协助走路 = 眼镜协助观看crutch: support 枴杖用来支持 【记】音：胯支，支持胯的枴杖；clutch 离合器或及操纵杆，都是杆子 crutch (n.)  Old English crycce ""crutch, staff,"" from Proto-Germanic *krukjo (cognates: Old Saxon krukka, Middle Dutch crucke, Old High German krucka, German Kröcke ""crutch,"" related to Old Norse krokr ""hook;"" see crook). Figurative sense is first recorded c.1600. As a verb, from 1640s. Italian gruccia ""crutch,"" crocco ""hook"" are Germanic loan-words."
